{"TopicId":221298,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Research and Development Centre UI (tech tree) not scaling To Ultrawide Screen (3440 x 1440 and other)","CreatedByName":"ChrisShourai","CreatedById":226083,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-19T18:40:48Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ChrisShourai","CreatedById":226083,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-19T18:40:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 Home 64-bit | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 7 3800X | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A04095MB NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3070 Ti (Gigabyte) | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32.0GB Dual-Channel Unknown @ 1333MHz (20-19-19-44)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I go into the R\u0026amp;D center while playing on my native 3440x1440 monitor and resolution, the tech tree does not cover the entire screen. If it is not meant to scale (it should, though... just increase the distance between the nodes but keep the nodes the same size), then at least have it centered. Thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022KerbalSpaceProgram22023-12-1911_35_34AM.png.e91baacdfbe7bab31a4dbcfeaa16fa70.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_12/KerbalSpaceProgram22023-12-1911_35_34AM.png.e91baacdfbe7bab31a4dbcfeaa16fa70.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-29T12:18:47Z\u0022 title=\u002212/29/2023 12:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 29\u0022\u003EDecember 29, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Spicat\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anonymous Bug Reporter","CreatedById":231013,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-19T19:48:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0W11 x64 Pro | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0I9-13900k | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0RTX4090 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn Ultrawide the UI is broken as the elements are not anchored\u00A0 to the left and do not autoscale.\u003Cbr\u003E\nEven on a 16:9 screen if you play windowed mode and change the windows to a different wider ratio this also occurs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee video for explanation:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/4-FJF1qwkvQ?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Kerbal Space Program 2 - Science Update Issues 1\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTested on 3840x1600, 3440x1440 and 2560x1080 Ultrawide\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlso happening on Windowed mode with wider window settings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Userguy1","CreatedById":173357,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-19T19:37:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe background image also does not fill the screen if you scroll over to Tier 4.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Possemaster","CreatedById":23006,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-19T19:55:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame issue:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/4-FJF1qwkvQ?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Kerbal Space Program 2 - Science Update Issues 1\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTested on 3840x1600, 3440x1440 and\u00A0 2560x1080\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlso happens in windowed mode on wider screen settings\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pvtHenk","CreatedById":228226,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-20T12:51:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0irrelevant | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0irrelevant | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0irrelevant | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003Eirrelevant\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScrolling all the way to the right on a widescreen monitor (3440 x 1440) reveals \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(excuse the brightness. windows snipping tool and HDR don\u00